---
title: Rachel’s Roast Celeriac and Beetroot Springtime Salad
description: Some people have a thing about not tempting fate. We reckon life should be the exact opposite - tempt fate to do what you want at every opportunity! That’s why Chef Rachel put together this Springtime salad. Warming enough to ward off the chills but with a distinct hint of sunnier times thrown in. Hello fate. Hello springtime.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/54ff03bc6ced6eb4088b457d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/54ff03bc6ced6eb4088b457d.pdf
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 613 kcal
  fat: 29 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 61 g
  protein: 27 g
cuisine: European
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/rachels-roast-celeriac-and-beetroot-springtime-salad-54ff03bc6ced6eb4088b457d
servings: 2
---

Pre-heat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Peel the @celeriac{2} using your #knife{} to follow the edge of the celeriac. Chop the celeriac into 1cm cubes. Peel the @beetroot{1} and cut into wedges.

Toss the celeriac and beetroot separately in 1 tbsp of @oil{1%tbsp}. Season with ¼ tsp of @salt{1/4%tsp}, @pepper{} and the leaves from the sprigs of @thyme{2%sprigs}. Roast in the oven for ~{20-25%minutes}, turning halfway through cooking.

> Toss the celeriac first then the beetroot to avoid everything turning pink!

Rinse the @quinoa{1/2%cup} under cold running water. Put the quinoa in a large #pot{} of cold water and bring to a gentle boil with half the @vegetable stock pot{1/2}. Cook for ~{15%minutes} from cold, until the quinoa is just, just tender. Drain the quinoa, put back in the dry warm #pan{}, cover with a #tea towel{} and keep to one side.

Make a dressing with the @honey{1%tbsp}, @red wine vinegar{1%tbsp}, 2 tbsp oil and salt and pepper to taste.

Toast the @hazelnuts{1%handful} in a dry pan. Allow to cool and then bash into small pieces using the base of a pan.

> As always, watch them like a hawk as they can burn easily.

When the beetroot and celeriac are cooked and golden brown remove from the oven and allow to cool slightly.

Toss the quinoa with the roasted veg, vinaigrette and at the last minute the @wild rocket{1%handful}. Serve topped with crumbled @goat's cheese{1%log} and the toasted hazelnuts.